message.content: It's difficult to definitively say which political party is "less bad" as it largely depends on individual beliefs and values. However, some may argue that Republicans tend to prioritize smaller government and fiscal responsibility, while Democrats often focus more on social welfare programs and equality. Libertarians generally advocate for minimal government intervention in both economic and personal matters. Ultimately, the best choice would depend on your own political ideology and what you believe is most important to society as a whole.
